&lt;p style=&quot;color: #666666;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;por Juan Luis Landaeta (*)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: #666666;&quot;&gt;Ilaina nasceu na Venezuela, filha de um casal que fugiu da ditadura argentina. Cresceu com convic&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es pessoais de quem &amp;eacute; testemunha da vida no ex&amp;iacute;lio. Frente a isso, ficou claro que queria uma mudan&amp;ccedil;a e queria ser parte dela. Aos 14 anos come&amp;ccedil;ou sua capacita&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o n&amp;atilde;o-formal em temas de direitos humanos e posteriormente cursou Estudos Internacionais e Comunica&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Social. No entanto, sempre sentiu que faltava algo dentro da forma&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o acad&amp;ecirc;mica regular.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Havia uma grande brecha entre o que as universidades estavam oferecendo e o que setor social estava precisando. As universidades em geral n&amp;atilde;o estavam oferecendo uma educa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o pr&amp;aacute;tica real&amp;rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Por sentir que n&amp;atilde;o havia um trabalho profundo de autoconhecimento nas universidades, ela come&amp;ccedil;ou a idear uma nova proposta a partir das premissas: &amp;ldquo;N&amp;atilde;o podemos viver uma vida pequena. Voc&amp;ecirc; tem que se conectar com o que acontece&amp;rdquo; e &amp;ldquo;&amp;Eacute; muito dif&amp;iacute;cil amar o que n&amp;atilde;o se conhece. Temos que conhecer&amp;rdquo;. Assim come&amp;ccedil;ou uma incans&amp;aacute;vel trajet&amp;oacute;ria que incluiu Haiti, Equador, Bol&amp;iacute;via e Qu&amp;ecirc;nia como destinos.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Em 2011, enquanto trabalhava no Programa Avancemos de Ashoka, um programa especialmente focado na sua maior paix&amp;atilde;o: os jovens, conheceu Roshan Paul. E &amp;eacute; assim que nos corredores da maior organiza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de empreendedorismo social do mundo que nasceria Amani Institute. O objetivo seria treinar profissionais para resolver problemas mundiais por meio de tr&amp;ecirc;s pilares:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: #666666;&quot;&gt;Experi&amp;ecirc;ncia: qualquer curso ou programa de Amani reside na pr&amp;aacute;tica, em aprender a fazer por meio do failure (erro).&lt;br /&gt;
Expertise: fortalecer as habilidades e ferramentas pr&amp;oacute;prias de cada um, n&amp;atilde;o se baseando somente em teorias, mas sim em uma vis&amp;atilde;o sist&amp;eacute;mica, emp&amp;aacute;tica, gerando coragem e capacidade de gest&amp;atilde;o de projetos que melhorem a capacidade de resolver problemas.&lt;br /&gt;
Conhecimento de um agente de mudan&amp;ccedil;as: envolver os valores e o estilo de vida, &amp;eacute; parte de um treino para ser humanamente sustent&amp;aacute;vel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: #666666;&quot;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Em Nair&amp;oacute;bi, foi inaugurado o primeiro HUB do Amani Institute, uma vez que tanto Ilaina como Roshan consideravam que era necess&amp;aacute;rio sair da &amp;aacute;rea de conforto para conseguir o verdadeiro esp&amp;iacute;rito de inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o. Em 2013, desenvolveram uma p&amp;oacute;s-gradua&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o em inova&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o social e atualmente desenham ter laborat&amp;oacute;rios de ideias e solu&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es na Am&amp;eacute;rica Latina, &amp;Aacute;frica e &amp;Aacute;sia. Nesse sentido, acaba de ser inaugurado o HUB em S&amp;atilde;o Paulo.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Ilaina comenta que a juventude oferece sobretudo a esperan&amp;ccedil;a e isso a alegra. Acima da criatividade ou da imagina&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o, que n&amp;atilde;o devem nunca cair, se v&amp;ecirc; a esperan&amp;ccedil;a. &amp;ldquo;Os jovens sentem que tudo &amp;eacute; poss&amp;iacute;vel, para mim isso &amp;eacute; muito certo, tudo &amp;eacute; poss&amp;iacute;vel&amp;rdquo;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Como atual jurada do concurso on-line &amp;ldquo;Jovens Desenhando Novas Realidades&amp;rdquo; da NEXSO em parceria com a Funda&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o Mi Sangre, ela insiste que se deve promover a paz como uma quest&amp;atilde;o global, e de fato, Amani significa &amp;ldquo;paz&amp;rdquo; no sentido amplo de n&amp;atilde;o conflito, estabilidade e alinhamento. Ressalta ainda que qualquer iniciativa para promo&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de ideias e trabalho conjunto n&amp;atilde;o &amp;eacute; somente positiva como necess&amp;aacute;ria.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;(*) Escritor e Embaixador da Ashoka Venezuela em Nova York. &amp;Eacute; advogado formado pela Universidad Cat&amp;oacute;lica Andr&amp;eacute;s Bello, 2012, e atualmente cursa Mestrado em Escrita Criativa em Espanhol oferecido pela New York University. Tamb&amp;eacute;m &amp;eacute; Editor Associado da Revista ViceVersa.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

NewsArticle.Article:
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &lt;em&gt;by Juan Luis Landaeta (*)&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ilaina was born in Venezuela,  daughter of an Argentinian couple who escaped from the Argentinian dictatorship during the ‘70s. She grew up with the beliefs of a person who was born in exile. Since she was a little girl, she has had a clear understanding that she wanted to see change, and that she wanted to be part of it. At the age of 14 she started learning about human rights, and later on she studied social communication and international affairs. However, she always felt something was missing within the regular academic environment. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
“There was a big gap between what universities offer and what the social sector needed. Universities were not providing a real practical education,” she says.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
She felt universities didn’t promote deep self-knowledge or awareness of oneself, so she designed a new proposal based on two premises: “We can’t live a small life. We have to get connected with what is happening,” and “It is very difficult to love what we don’t know. We need to know ourselves.” That’s how her non-stop journey started; a journey that took Iliana to destinations as diverse as Haiti, Ecuador, Bolivia, the USA, Kenya and Brazil. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In 2011, while she was working at Ashoka’s Youth Venture program, which focuses on her passion: young people, she met Roshan Paul. And that’s how, in the hallways of the world’s biggest social entrepreneurship organization, the Amani Institute was born. Its goal was to train young professionals to solve global problems under three pillars:&lt;br&gt;
1) Experience: All courses and programs are based on real, practical experiences, learning by doing through failure. &lt;br&gt;
2) Expertise: Strengthen each person’s skills and tools, not only based on theories, but on a systemic vision that is empathetic, fosters courage, and builds project management skills in order to improve the ability to solve problems. &lt;br&gt;
3) Changemaker knowledge: Involves values, lifestyle, and being part of training in how to be a sustainable human being. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
The first HUB of Amani Institute opened its doors in Nairobi, Kenya; both Iliana and Roshan believe it is necessary to get out of one’s comfort zone in order to promote a real spirit of innovation, and that’s what they did. In 2013 they launched a postgraduate degree in Social Innovation, and they aspire to establish laboratories for ideas and solutions in Latin America, Africa and Asia. The first HUB in Latin America is based in Sao Paulo, Brazil. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Ilaina says that youth offers hope, and she is happy to know this. Above creativity and imagination, which should also be ever-present, stands hope. “Young people believe everything is possible, and that’s so true for me as well. Everything is possible,” she says.  &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
As a judge for the “Youth Designing New Realities” online competition, she insists that peace should be promoted as a global issue, In fact, “Amani” means “peace” in the broadest sense of stability, alignment, and no conflict. She points out that any initiative to promote new ideas and collaborative work is not only positive but necessary. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;em&gt;(*) Writer and Ambassador of Ashoka Venezuela in New York. He is a lawyer from Universidad Cat&#243;lica Andr&#233;s Bello and is currently part of the Creative Writing Master Degree of  New  York  University. Associate Editor of ViceVersa Magazine.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;por&amp;nbsp;Juan Luis Landaeta (*)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;color: inherit;&quot;&gt;Ilaina naci&amp;oacute; en Venezuela, hija de un matrimonio que huy&amp;oacute; de la dictadura argentina. Creci&amp;oacute; con las convicciones personales de quien es testigo de la vida en el exilio. Frente a esta circunstancia, tuvo claro que quer&amp;iacute;a un cambio y quer&amp;iacute;a ser parte de &amp;eacute;l. A los 14 a&amp;ntilde;os empez&amp;oacute; su capacitaci&amp;oacute;n no formal en temas de Derechos Humanos y posteriormente curs&amp;oacute; Estudios Internacionales y Comunicaci&amp;oacute;n Social. Sin embargo, siempre sinti&amp;oacute; que faltaba algo dentro de la formaci&amp;oacute;n acad&amp;eacute;mica regular.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Hab&amp;iacute;a una gran brecha entre lo que las universidades estaban ofreciendo y lo que el sector social estaba necesitando. Las universidades en general no estaban dando una ense&amp;ntilde;anza pr&amp;aacute;ctica real&amp;rdquo;. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Por sentir que no hab&amp;iacute;a un trabajo profundo de autoconocimiento en las universidades, empez&amp;oacute; a idear una nueva propuesta bajo las premisas: &amp;ldquo;No podemos vivir la vida peque&amp;ntilde;a. Hay que conectarse con lo que sucede&amp;rdquo; y &amp;ldquo;Es muy dif&amp;iacute;cil amar lo que uno no conoce. Tenemos que conocernos&amp;rdquo;. As&amp;iacute; empez&amp;oacute; una incansable trayectoria que incluye a Hait&amp;iacute;, Ecuador, Bolivia y Kenia como destinos.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
En 2011, mientras trabajaba en el programa Avancemos de Ashoka, un programa especialmente enfocado en lo que era su mayor pasi&amp;oacute;n: los j&amp;oacute;venes, conoci&amp;oacute; a Roshan Paul. Y es as&amp;iacute; que en los pasillos de la mayor organizaci&amp;oacute;n de emprendimiento social del mundo nacer&amp;iacute;a Amani Institute. El objetivo ser&amp;iacute;a entrenar profesionales para resolver problemas mundiales bajo tres pilares:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1) Experiencia: cualquier curso o programa de Amani radica en la pr&amp;aacute;ctica, en aprender del hacer a trav&amp;eacute;s del failure (error). &lt;br /&gt;
2) Experticia: fortalecer las habilidades y herramientas propias de cada quien, no bas&amp;aacute;ndose solo en teor&amp;iacute;as, sino en una visi&amp;oacute;n sist&amp;eacute;mica, emp&amp;aacute;tica, generando coraje y capacidad de manejo de proyectos que mejoren la capacidad de resolver problemas. &lt;br /&gt;
3) Conocimiento de un agente de cambio: involucrar los valores, y el estilo de vida, se parte de un entrenamiento de ser sustentable a nivel humano. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
En Nairobi se abri&amp;oacute; el primer HUB de Amani Institute, ya que tanto Ilaina como Roshan consideraban que era necesario salir del &amp;aacute;rea de confort para conseguir el verdadero esp&amp;iacute;ritu de innovaci&amp;oacute;n En 2013 desarrollaron un Post Grado en Innovaci&amp;oacute;n Social y actualmente desean tener laboratorios de ideas y soluciones en Am&amp;eacute;rica Latina, &amp;Aacute;frica y Asia. De hecho, acaba de ser inaugurado el HUB en Sao Paul. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Ilaina comenta que la juventud ofrece sobre todo esperanza y la alegra saberlo. Por encima de la creatividad o la imaginaci&amp;oacute;n, que no deben caer nunca, ve la esperanza. &amp;ldquo;Los j&amp;oacute;venes sienten que todo es posible, para m&amp;iacute; eso es muy cierto, todo se puede&amp;rdquo;. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Como actual jurado del concurso online &amp;ldquo;J&amp;oacute;venes dibujando nuevas realidades&amp;rdquo; de NEXSO junto a Fundaci&amp;oacute;n Mi Sangre, insiste en que se debe promover la paz como una cuesti&amp;oacute;n global, de hecho, Amani significa &amp;ldquo;paz&amp;rdquo; en un sentido amplio de no conflicto, estabilidad y alineaci&amp;oacute;n. Resalta que cualquier iniciativa hacia la promoci&amp;oacute;n de ideas y trabajo conjunto no es solo positiva sino necesaria. &lt;br /&gt;
