&lt;p&gt;Yann Borgstedt joined&amp;nbsp;NEXSO as a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www5.iadb.org/mif/nexso/en-us/judges.aspx&quot;&gt;judge&lt;/a&gt; on the competition&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;Solutions that Transform Latin America and the Caribbean&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Supporting disadvantaged women and girls&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In his words, &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;A few years ago, I wanted to find ways of bringing hope for a better future to children and adults in developing countries. After careful research I decided to launch an organization dedicated to empowering disadvantaged women and girls&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Womanity Foundation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Womanity Foundation believes that by directly supporting women and girls, they are reducing inequalities and fostering progress for everyone.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
